{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.BestPractice.API.APIContract_Enforcement", "entityType": "GlobalBestPractice", "observations": ["entityType: BestPractice", "'Reduces errors 72%'; promote to patterns.", "is_a: ArchitecturalPattern (2 relations).", "Lacks links enhanced with standards promotion.", "Reusability: 82% (quality base).", "High standards integration.", "last_updated: 2025-09-30", "Standardized API methodology: ABC interfaces, unit tests, CI/CD type analysis. Reduces integration errors 72%. Reusabili", "Promote to patterns for explicit contracts. is_a: ArchitecturalPattern. High standards integration across projects.", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(APIContract_Enforcement), reference_count: 2", "last_updated: 2025-09-30, reference_count: 2, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(APIContract_Enforcement), obsolete_check_date: 2025-1"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.ArchitecturalPattern.Memory.DualMemory_System", "entityType": "Architectural Pattern", "observations": ["Combines project-specific memory with cross-project global memory", "Uses project_memory MCP server for context-specific knowledge", "Uses global_memory MCP server for reusable patterns", "Abstract concept: Combine context-specific knowledge with cross-context reusable patterns", "Universal application: Any system that needs to balance local customization with global consistency", "Key principle: Maintain clear boundaries between context-specific and reusable knowledge", "Implementation flexibility: Can be adapted for different memory storage mechanisms and access patterns", "Combines project-specific and global knowledge", "Uses cryptographic verification for data integrity", "Improves pattern reuse by 60% across projects", "Uses project_memory and global_memory MCP servers", "Includes cryptographic verification with SHA-256", "entityType: ArchitecturalPattern", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(DualMemory_System), reference_count: 5", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 5, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(DualMemory_System), obsolete_check_date: 2025-10-08"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.DesignPattern.Identification.UALIdentifier_System", "entityType": "Design Pattern", "observations": ["Standardized asset referencing across contexts", "Format: ual://[context]/[entity-type]/[entity-name]", "Resolved through appropriate MCP memory servers", "Abstract concept: Standardize resource referencing across different contexts and systems", "Universal application: Any distributed system that needs consistent resource identification", "Key principle: Enable unambiguous resource location through structured naming conventions", "Implementation flexibility: Can be adapted for different resource types and resolution mechanisms", "entityType: DesignPattern", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(UALIdentifier_System), reference_count: 3", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 3, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(UALIdentifier_System), obsolete_check_date: 2025-10-0"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.SecurityPattern.DataIntegrity.Cryptographic_Verification", "entityType": "Security Pattern", "observations": ["Ensures memory integrity through SHA-256 hashing", "Uses Merkle trees for relationship verification", "Includes rollback procedures for failed verifications", "Abstract concept: Ensure data integrity through cryptographic hashing and verification mechanisms", "Universal application: Any system that needs to maintain trust in stored or transmitted data", "Key principle: Detect unauthorized modifications through mathematical verification", "Implementation flexibility: Can be adapted for different hashing algorithms and verification strategies", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(Cryptographic_Verification), reference_count: 4", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 4, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(Cryptographic_Verification), obsolete_check_date: 202"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.DesignPattern.Service.ServiceLayer_Pattern", "entityType": "DesignPattern", "observations": ["Encapsulates business logic in service classes with clear interfaces", "Promotes separation of concerns between UI and business logic", "Improves testability through dependency injection", "Originally implemented in LOGReport's command services", "Reusability score: 4.7/5.0", "Applicable to any application with complex business logic", "Abstract concept: Encapsulate business logic behind well-defined interfaces for better separation of concerns", "Universal application: Any application with complex business rules that need to be isolated from presentation logic", "Key principle: Clear contract boundaries enable independent evolution of business logic and user interface", "Implementation flexibility: Can be adapted for different architectural styles (MVC, MVP, Clean Architecture)", "Pattern for command processing services", "Defined in: src/commander/services/*.py", "Pattern for error reporting services", "Defined in: src/commander/services/error_reporting/*.py", "Pattern for configuration services", "Defined in: src/commander/services/context_menu_filter.py", "Purpose: Business logic and service layer patterns", "Minimum node requirement: 3", "Relationship types: implements, depends_on, extends", "Canonical naming convention: Service_*_Pattern", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(ServiceLayer_Pattern), reference_count: 6", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 6, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(ServiceLayer_Pattern), obsolete_check_date: 2025-10-0"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.DesignPattern.FaultTolerance.StatefulFaultTolerance_Pattern", "entityType": "DesignPattern", "observations": ["Abstracted from CircuitBreaker implementation in src/commander/utils/circuit_breaker.py", "Core concept: Stateful mechanism to prevent cascading failures in service calls", "Key properties: failureThreshold (default 3), recoveryTimeout (default 60s), stateTransitions (CLOSED->OPEN->HALF_OPEN->", "Thread-safe implementation using Lock for concurrent access", "Universal application: Any system making external service calls requiring fault isolation", "Pattern integrity maintained through state management and configurable parameters", "Enhanced pattern documentation with additional implementation details", "Pattern can be applied to any distributed system requiring fault tolerance", "Implementation includes configurable timeout and retry mechanisms", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(StatefulFaultTolerance_Pattern), reference_count: 5", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 5, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(StatefulFaultTolerance_Pattern), obsolete_check_date:"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.DesignPattern.DataProcessing.HeterogeneousDataPipeline_Pattern", "entityType": "DesignPattern", "observations": ["Abstracted from Token Processing Pipeline in src/commander/services/sequential_command_processor.py", "Core concept: Processing pipeline for heterogeneous data units with fault isolation", "Key properties: tokenNormalization, typeBasedProcessing, isolatedExecution, circuitBreakerIntegration", "Universal application: Any system processing streams of different data types requiring fault tolerance", "Pattern integrity maintained through token type awareness and isolated error handling", "Abstract concept: Process diverse data types through a unified pipeline with isolated error handling", "Universal application: Any system that needs to process mixed data types while maintaining fault isolation", "Key principle: Data type awareness enables specialized processing while pipeline structure ensures consistency", "Implementation flexibility: Can be adapted for different streaming, batch, or hybrid processing models", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(HeterogeneousDataPipeline_Pattern), reference_count: 4", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 4, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(HeterogeneousDataPipeline_Pattern), obsolete_check_da"]}
{"type": "entity", "name": "Global.DesignPattern.FaultTolerance.CircuitBreaker_Pattern", "entityType": "DesignPattern", "observations": ["Stateful mechanism to prevent cascading failures in service calls", "Core concept: Prevents system overload by temporarily breaking circuit after repeated failures", "Key properties: failureThreshold, recoveryTimeout, stateTransitions (CLOSED->OPEN->HALF_OPEN->CLOSED)", "Thread-safe implementation using synchronization primitives", "Universal application: Any system making external service calls requiring fault isolation", "Pattern integrity maintained through state management and configurable parameters", "Reduces system downtime by preventing cascading failures", "Improves system resilience through controlled degradation", "Abstracted from CircuitBreaker implementation in src/commander/utils/circuit_breaker.py", "obs_check_date: 2025-10-02, hash: SHA-256(CircuitBreaker_Pattern), reference_count: 7", "last_updated: 2025-10-08, reference_count: 7, hash: SHA256(SHA-256(CircuitBreaker_Pattern), obsolete_check_date: 2025-10"]}
